<h2 id="features">Features</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Thanks to CSS framework Foundation, the site is mobile friendly.</li>
  <li>Highly customizable.</li>
  <li>Clear code syntax</li>
  <li>Support both Page and Post layouts.</li>
  <li>Enable Disqus comment.</li>
  <li>Custom code for centered and captioned images.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="get-started">Get started</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Fork the repository.</li>
  <li>Clone the repository: <code>git clone https://github.com/&lt;YOUR USERNAME&gt;/zebra</code></li>
  <li>Install the GitHub Pages gem (included Jekyll): <code>bundle install</code></li>
  <li>Start the Jekyll server: <code>jekyll server --watch</code></li>
  <li>Open http://127.0.0.1:4000/ or http://localhost:4000/</li>
</ol>

